## 6. Implementation — narrated, class by class

**`models.py` — value objects, enums, errors.** These are the immutable nouns. Money lives in **integer cents** so we never accumulate float drift; `User`/`Split`/`Expense` are frozen dataclasses so they're safe to share across threads later.

```python
class SplitType(Enum):
    EQUAL = "EQUAL"; EXACT = "EXACT"; PERCENT = "PERCENT"

class SplitwiseError(Exception): ...
class UserNotFoundError(SplitwiseError): ...
class InvalidAmountError(SplitwiseError): ...
class InvalidSplitError(SplitwiseError): ...
class DuplicateExpenseError(SplitwiseError): ...

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class User:
    id: str; name: str; email: str

