> 💬 "Strategies are stateless, so the factory hands back shared singletons — no per-call allocation."

**`expense_manager.py` — the orchestrator/ledger.** It owns the `balance[a][b]` nested map (the source of truth), validates everything at the boundary, then applies splits.

```python
class ExpenseManager:
    def __init__(self):
        self._users = {}
        self._expenses = {}
        self._balance = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int))  # balance[a][b] = a owes b

    def add_expense(self, expense_id, description, amount, paid_by,
                    split_type, participants, values=None):
        if expense_id in self._expenses:
            raise DuplicateExpenseError(f"expense {expense_id} already exists")
        amount_cents = to_cents(amount)
        if amount_cents <= 0: raise InvalidAmountError("amount must be positive")
        if not participants: raise InvalidAmountError("need at least one participant")
        if len(set(participants)) != len(participants):
            raise InvalidAmountError("duplicate participant in expense")
        self._require_user(paid_by)
        for uid in participants: self._require_user(uid)

        strategy = SplitStrategyFactory.get_strategy(split_type)
        splits = strategy.compute(amount_cents, participants, values)

        for split in splits:
            if split.user_id == paid_by: continue
            self._add_debt(debtor=split.user_id, creditor=paid_by, cents=split.amount_cents)
        expense = Expense(expense_id, description, amount_cents, paid_by,
                          tuple(splits), time.time())
        self._expenses[expense_id] = expense
        return expense

    def _add_debt(self, debtor, creditor, cents):
        self._balance[debtor][creditor] += cents
        self._balance[creditor][debtor] -= cents

    def settle(self, payer, payee, amount):
        self._require_user(payer); self._require_user(payee)
        cents = to_cents(amount)
        if cents <= 0: raise InvalidAmountError("settlement must be positive")
        self._add_debt(debtor=payee, creditor=payer, cents=cents)
```

> 💬 "The whole correctness story is in `_add_debt`: I always touch *both* directions, so `balance[a][b] == -balance[b][a]` is an invariant by construction. And I validate *everything* — duplicate id, amount, unknown users — **before** I mutate the ledger, so a rejected expense leaves zero side effects. That's how I guarantee no request is ever silently half-applied."

> 💬 "Settlement is elegant: a payment is just the *opposite* of a debt, so I reuse `_add_debt` with the roles flipped — no second code path to keep in sync."

